article.headline: Montana St. 70, E. Washington 68
article.story: BOZEMAN, Mont. -- Flavien Davis scored 19 points and Montana State overcame a 15-point deficit in the second half to beat Eastern Washington 70-68 in overtime Saturday night. Calen Coleman made a 3-pointer in overtime to put the Bobcats (5-7, 2-2 Big Sky) ahead to stay at 67-66 with 3:10 to go. Xavier Blount scored 14 points and Christian Moon scored 12 for Montana State. Coleman finished with 11 points. Davis had 12 points in the second half when the Bobcats overcame a 50-35 deficit. The game was 64-all headed to overtime. Jeffrey Forbes led Eastern Washington (3-11, 1-3) with 18 points. Kevin Winford had 13 points and six assists for the Eagles.
